{{Multiple issues|{{refimprove|date=February 2017}}{{notability|date=February 2017}} }}
A '''Plant Information Management System''' (PIMS) collects and integrates information about a production process from different sources.<ref>Kraft, Theresa (2008). ''Systematic and holistic IT Project Management approach for commercial software with case studies''. ''Information Systems Education Journal'' 6(63)</ref>
==Overview== ===Tasks=== Important tasks of a PIMS are:
* Company-wide gather, consolidate and process data * Analysis of production performance, product quality, process capacity and control compliance. * Provide [[Key Performance Indicator]] (KPI) to improve decision-making processes * [[Business reporting|Reporting]] for decision support and documentation * Consolidation of data from different sources ([[Enterprise Resource Planning]] (ERP), Laboratory, [[Distributed Control System]] (DCS)...) * Integration of off-line data (laboratory, calculations, future load profiles) * Access via the company-wide [[intranet]] also from offices. Via Web (Thin client) or Tcp / Ip (Fat client) * Enriching / refining raw data * Event-driven calculations * Long-term archiving of data and reports (over many years)
===Manufacturers=== Manufacturers are: * [[Aspen Technology|Aspen Tech]] InfoPlus.21 (IP.21) * [[OSIsoft|Osisoft]] PI * [[Honeywell]] PHD * [[Wonderware]] Historian * GeFanuc iHistorian * Yokogawa Exaquantum * [[Capstone Technology|Capstone Technology]] dataPARC * Elipse Plant Manager
==Subdivisions== There are the following subdivisions: * SQL / desktop systems * [[SCADA]] Historian * Enterprise Historian
==See also== * [[Data acquisition]] * [[Data collection system]] * [[Totally integrated automation]]
